EXAMPLE:
The following example deletes the data from column 2 from a spreadsheet.<br>&lt;!--- Get the spreadsheet data as a query. ---&gt; 
&lt;cfquery 
       name=&quot;courses&quot; datasource=&quot;cfdocexamples&quot; 
       cachedwithin=&quot;#CreateTimeSpan(0, 6, 0, 0)#&quot;&gt; 
       SELECT CORNUMBER,DEPT_ID,COURSE_ID,CORNAME 
       FROM COURSELIST 
&lt;/cfquery&gt; 
 
&lt;cfscript&gt; 
    ///We need an absolute path, so get the current directory path. 
    theFile=GetDirectoryFromPath(GetCurrentTemplatePath()) &amp; courses.xls&quot;; 
    //Create a new Excel spreadsheet object and add the query data. 
    theSheet = SpreadsheetNew(&quot;CourseData&quot;); 
 
    SpreadsheetAddRows(theSheet,courses); 
    //Delete the second column of the sheet. 
    <strong>SpreadsheetDeleteColumn(theSheet,2);</strong> 
&lt;/cfscript&gt; 
 
&lt;!--- Write the spreadsheet to a file, replacing any existing file. ---&gt; 
&lt;cfspreadsheet action=&quot;write&quot; filename=&quot;#theFile#&quot; name=&quot;theSheet&quot;  
    sheet=1 sheetname=&quot;courses&quot; overwrite=true&gt;<br>
